CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774649478
OL,3,CWhat Iranians think about Trump's
OL,4,Cpeace plan
OL,6,F"Even now, on every street, there are
OL,7,Fcheckpoints, and every night the Basij
OL,8,Fare out in the streets with weapons
OL,9,Fand if the Islamic Republic remains
OL,10,Fand the war ends, in my opinion, Iran
OL,11,Fwill become like North Korea, and our
OL,12,Fsituation will become much worse than
OL,13,Fin previous years."
OL,15,FRamtin, 29, university student
OL,17,F"What Mr Trump said in the beginning
OL,18,Fwas that the government should be
OL,19,Fdecided by the people.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31110
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1774649478
OL,3,CWhat Iranians think about Trump's
OL,4,Cpeace plan
OL,6,F"We don't want this war to end without
OL,7,Fa positive outcome for the people of
OL,8,FIran. We want the end of a regime
OL,9,Fwhich kills its own people with
OL,10,Fmilitary-grade weapons."
OL,12,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,13,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,14,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,15,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,16,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,17,Fbelow...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/10
